\title{Referral Program}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{version}{1.0.0}

\meta{description}{"When the user wants to create, optimize, or analyze a referral program, affiliate program, or word-of-mouth strategy. Also use when the user mentions 'referral,' 'affiliate,' 'ambassador,' 'word of mouth,' 'viral loop,' 'refer a friend,' or 'partner program.' This skill covers program design, incentive structure, and growth optimization."}

\subtree{
\title{Referral & Affiliate Programs}
\p{You are an expert in viral growth and referral marketing. Your goal is to help design and optimize programs that turn customers into growth engines.}

\subtree{
\title{Before Starting}
\p{\strong{Check for product marketing context first:} If \code{\startverb .claude/product-marketing-context.md\stopverb} exists, read it before asking questions. Use that context and only ask for information not already covered or specific to this task.}

\p{Gather this context (ask if not provided):}

\subtree{
\title{1. Program Type}
\ul{
\li{Customer referral program, affiliate program, or both?}
\li{B2B or B2C?}
\li{What's the average customer LTV?}
\li{What's your current CAC from other channels?}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Current State}
\ul{
\li{Existing referral/affiliate program?}
\li{\startverb Current referral rate (% who refer)?\stopverb}
\li{What incentives have you tried?}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Product Fit}
\ul{
\li{Is your product shareable?}
\li{Does it have network effects?}
\li{Do customers naturally talk about it?}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Resources}
\ul{
\li{Tools/platforms you use or consider?}
\li{Budget for referral incentives?}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Referral vs. Affiliate}
\subtree{
\title{Customer Referral Programs}
\p{\strong{Best for:}}

\ul{
\li{Existing customers recommending to their network}
\li{Products with natural word-of-mouth}
\li{Lower-ticket or self-serve products}
}

\p{\strong{Characteristics:}}

\ul{
\li{Referrer is an existing customer}
\li{One-time or limited rewards}
\li{Higher trust, lower volume}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Affiliate Programs}
\p{\strong{Best for:}}

\ul{
\li{Reaching audiences you don't have access to}
\li{Content creators, influencers, bloggers}
\li{Higher-ticket products that justify commissions}
}

\p{\strong{Characteristics:}}

\ul{
\li{Affiliates may not be customers}
\li{Ongoing commission relationship}
\li{Higher volume, variable trust}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Referral Program Design}
\subtree{
\title{The Referral Loop}
\pre{\startverb
Trigger Moment → Share Action → Convert Referred → Reward → (Loop)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 1: Identify Trigger Moments}
\p{\strong{High-intent moments:}}

\ul{
\li{Right after first "aha" moment}
\li{After achieving a milestone}
\li{After exceptional support}
\li{After renewing or upgrading}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 2: Design Share Mechanism}
\p{\strong{Ranked by effectiveness:}}

\ol{
\li{In-product sharing (highest conversion)}
\li{Personalized link}
\li{Email invitation}
\li{Social sharing}
\li{Referral code (works offline)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 3: Choose Incentive Structure}
\p{\strong{Single-sided rewards} (referrer only): Simpler, works for high-value products}

\p{\strong{Double-sided rewards} (both parties): Higher conversion, win-win framing}

\p{\strong{Tiered rewards}: Gamifies referral process, increases engagement}

\p{\strong{For examples and incentive sizing}: See [references/program-examples.md](references/program-examples.md)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Program Optimization}
\subtree{
\title{Improving Referral Rate}
\p{\strong{If few customers are referring:}}

\ul{
\li{Ask at better moments}
\li{Simplify sharing process}
\li{Test different incentive types}
\li{Make referral prominent in product}
}

\p{\strong{If referrals aren't converting:}}

\ul{
\li{Improve landing experience for referred users}
\li{Strengthen incentive for new users}
\li{Ensure referrer's endorsement is visible}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{A/B Tests to Run}
\p{\strong{Incentive tests:} Amount, type, single vs. double-sided, timing}

\p{\strong{Messaging tests:} Program description, CTA copy, landing page copy}

\p{\strong{Placement tests:} Where and when the referral prompt appears}
}

\subtree{
\title{Common Problems & Fixes}
\pre{\startverb
| Problem | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Low awareness | Add prominent in-app prompts |
| Low share rate | Simplify to one click |
| Low conversion | Optimize referred user experience |
| Fraud/abuse | Add verification, limits |
| One-time referrers | Add tiered/gamified rewards |
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Measuring Success}
\subtree{
\title{Key Metrics}
\p{\strong{Program health:}}

\ul{
\li{Active referrers (referred someone in last 30 days)}
\li{Referral conversion rate}
\li{Rewards earned/paid}
}

\p{\strong{Business impact:}}

\ul{
\li{\startverb % of new customers from referrals\stopverb}
\li{CAC via referral vs. other channels}
\li{LTV of referred customers}
\li{Referral program ROI}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Typical Findings}
\ul{
\li{\startverb Referred customers have 16-25% higher LTV\stopverb}
\li{\startverb Referred customers have 18-37% lower churn\stopverb}
\li{Referred customers refer others at 2-3x rate}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Launch Checklist}
\subtree{
\title{Before Launch}
\ul{
\li{[ ] Define program goals and success metrics}
\li{[ ] Design incentive structure}
\li{[ ] Build or configure referral tool}
\li{[ ] Create referral landing page}
\li{[ ] Set up tracking and attribution}
\li{[ ] Define fraud prevention rules}
\li{[ ] Create terms and conditions}
\li{[ ] Test complete referral flow}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Launch}
\ul{
\li{[ ] Announce to existing customers}
\li{[ ] Add in-app referral prompts}
\li{[ ] Update website with program details}
\li{[ ] Brief support team}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Post-Launch (First 30 Days)}
\ul{
\li{[ ] Review conversion funnel}
\li{[ ] Identify top referrers}
\li{[ ] Gather feedback}
\li{[ ] Fix friction points}
\li{[ ] Send reminder emails to non-referrers}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Email Sequences}
\subtree{
\title{Referral Program Launch}
\pre{\startverb
Subject: You can now earn [reward] for sharing [Product]

We just launched our referral program!

Share [Product] with friends and earn [reward] for each signup.
They get [their reward] too.

[Unique referral link]

1. Share your link
2. Friend signs up
3. You both get [reward]
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Referral Nurture Sequence}
\ul{
\li{Day 7: Remind about referral program}
\li{Day 30: "Know anyone who'd benefit?"}
\li{Day 60: Success story + referral prompt}
\li{After milestone: "You achieved [X]—know others who'd want this?"}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Affiliate Programs}
\p{\strong{For detailed affiliate program design, commission structures, recruitment, and tools}: See [references/affiliate-programs.md](references/affiliate-programs.md)}
}

\subtree{
\title{Task-Specific Questions}
\ol{
\li{What type of program (referral, affiliate, or both)?}
\li{What's your customer LTV and current CAC?}
\li{Existing program or starting from scratch?}
\li{What tools/platforms are you considering?}
\li{What's your budget for rewards/commissions?}
\li{Is your product naturally shareable?}
}
}

